Because std::vector can have any type of element, e.g. vector of 
vectors, the procedure has to be generic enough. So it is realized 
through iterators which are not exclusive for std::vector.
E.g. for vector of pairs <string, some_type> it is probably this 
procedure which will be called:
https://github.com/sgsokol/Rcpp/blob/acf8756a75a97ee203e261412a2ab3fa7d6e15c7/inst/include/Rcpp/internal/wrap.h#L334
It will produce a named list in R.

